51
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:00,919
before we really develop the entirety

52
00:02:00,919 --> 00:02:02,319
of the message this morning.

53
00:02:02,319 --> 00:02:03,800
But we find that Paul begins and he says,

54
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:07,919
moreover brethren, we do you to wit

55
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:12,919
of the grace of God bestowed on the churches of Macedonia.

56
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,600
And so as we begin, we find that the apostle Paul

57
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:20,000
is going to want the believers in Corinth.

58
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,800
This is the church that he's writing to.

59
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:24,360
God had used the apostle Paul to minister

60
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,860
to a number of different people.

61
00:02:26,559 --> 00:02:27,860
Here, he's writing to the church in Corinth,

62
00:02:27,860 --> 00:02:29,580
to the believers there in Corinth.

63
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:32,779
And he had the opportunity to take the gospel to Corinth

64
00:02:32,779 --> 00:02:35,100
at the end of his second missionary journey.

65
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:37,860
And we find that he faithfully served the Lord

66
00:02:37,860 --> 00:02:40,300
there in Corinth, the church was established

67
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:43,899
and now he's writing back to this local church.

68
00:02:43,899 --> 00:02:45,860
But at the end of verse number one,

69
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:48,339
he says that he wants to reference to them,

70
00:02:48,339 --> 00:02:50,380
he wants them to know, we do you to wit,

71
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:52,259
we want you to be knowledgeable of this,

72
00:02:52,259 --> 00:02:55,539
of what the grace of God bestowed

73
00:02:55,539 --> 00:02:58,220
on the churches of Macedonia.

74
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:02,419
God's grace was bestowed upon them, his enabling.

75
00:03:02,419 --> 00:03:04,580
We've talked about God's grace being sufficient

76
00:03:04,580 --> 00:03:07,339
as we've dealt with the subject throughout this year.

77
00:03:07,339 --> 00:03:10,339
And so now Paul is going to mention here

78
00:03:10,339 --> 00:03:13,779
in verse number one, the churches of Macedonia.

79
00:03:13,779 --> 00:03:15,539
That would be the church in Philippi,

80
00:03:15,539 --> 00:03:18,259
the church in Thessalonica, the church in Berea.

81
00:03:18,259 --> 00:03:20,539
And we find that he's referencing those churches

82
00:03:20,539 --> 00:03:22,979
and we find that it was in those cities as well

83
00:03:22,979 --> 00:03:25,539
that the Apostle Paul had the opportunity

84
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:27,500
to be able to minister to

85
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,699
during his second missionary journey.

86
00:03:29,699 --> 00:03:31,820
If we were to outline the second missionary journey

87
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:34,539
of the Apostle Paul and to understand the places

88
00:03:34,539 --> 00:03:36,619
in which he went, we would find that first he went

89
00:03:36,619 --> 00:03:39,380
to Philippi and then after being in Philippi,

90
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:42,139
he went to Thessalonica and after Thessalonica,

91
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:45,460
he went to Berea and then there was a stop in Athens.

92
00:03:45,460 --> 00:03:49,259
Remember, he went to Athens really for a time of refreshing

93
00:03:49,259 --> 00:03:52,419
but he saw a city that was wholly given to idolatry

94
00:03:52,419 --> 00:03:55,619
and he could not help himself but preach to them as well.

95
00:03:55,619 --> 00:03:56,979
And he said that he went through

96
00:03:56,979 --> 00:03:59,020
and he saw all of their idolatry.

97
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:01,779
He saw all of those things and as he's on Mars Hill,

98
00:04:01,779 --> 00:04:05,179
he says that there was an altar to the unknown God,

99
00:04:05,179 --> 00:04:07,380
him declare I unto you,

100
00:04:07,380 --> 00:04:10,020
and he preached the gospel there in Athens.

101
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:13,220
And then we find that Paul ends up in Corinth,

102
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:15,020
the church that's being written to here

103
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:16,179
in the passage of scripture.

104
00:04:16,179 --> 00:04:18,739
That's really the last stop, if you will,

105
00:04:18,739 --> 00:04:21,579
during the second missionary journey.

106
00:04:21,579 --> 00:04:24,579
As we begin to unfold and look at what's taking place,

107
00:04:24,579 --> 00:04:27,820
the Apostle Paul is going to, in the text of scripture,

108
00:04:27,820 --> 00:04:31,500
commend these churches in Macedonia,

109
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,260
so that would be the church at Philippi,

110
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:36,779
Thessalonica, Berea, and he's going to commend them

111
00:04:36,779 --> 00:04:38,940
with regard to their giving.

112
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:41,239
He says, as we look at the text of scripture,

113
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:45,200
that this church was giving and they were a great example

114
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:48,660
of what it was to be a giving church

115
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,339
and we find that they were to be an example,

116
00:04:51,339 --> 00:04:53,540
not only to the believers in Corinth

117
00:04:53,540 --> 00:04:55,420
and to that local church,

118
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:57,500
but we find that God has preserved it,

119
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:01,739
so really the churches of Macedonia provide for churches

120
00:05:01,739 --> 00:05:05,660
throughout the entirety of the church age a great example.

121
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:07,899
I've titled the message Exemplary Giving

122
00:05:07,899 --> 00:05:10,500
because that's what we see in the text of scripture.

123
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:14,220
And again, as we try to lay the setting

124
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,540
and kind of the background,

125
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:18,179
let's go to the book of Acts, if you will, very quickly

126
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:21,260
and look at Acts chapter number 11 with me.

127
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:24,299
And I want you to notice that in Acts chapter number 11,

128
00:05:24,299 --> 00:05:27,179
Paul has not yet taken his first missionary journey.

129
00:05:27,179 --> 00:05:28,700
The first missionary journey

130
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:31,540
actually doesn't take place until Acts 13.

131
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:32,459
So not only do we know

132
00:05:32,459 --> 00:05:34,339
that Paul's not taking his first missionary journey,

133
00:05:34,339 --> 00:05:37,019
obviously he's not taking a second or third either,

134
00:05:37,019 --> 00:05:38,820
but here in Acts chapter number 11,

135
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:41,299
God reveals something to us

136
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:43,380
about really what we're reading

137
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:45,179
in 2 Corinthians chapter number eight,

138
00:05:45,179 --> 00:05:47,779
and that is that Paul had been involved

139
00:05:47,779 --> 00:05:52,779
in this situation of giving and collecting of offerings

140
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:55,100
even before that first missionary journey.

141
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:58,019
Look in Acts chapter 11 in verse number 27.

142
00:05:58,019 --> 00:06:00,200
The Bible says, and in these days came prophets

143
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,140
from Jerusalem unto Antioch.

144
00:06:02,140 --> 00:06:04,220
That's where Paul was.

145
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:06,179
And we find that the Bible says in verse 28,

146
00:06:06,179 --> 00:06:08,700
there stood up one of them named Agabus

147
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,739
and signified by the spirit

148
00:06:10,739 --> 00:06:13,140
that there should be great dearth throughout all the world,

149
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:16,420
which came to pass in the days of Claudius Caesar.

150
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:17,940
Notice the Bible says in verse 29,

151
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:22,380
then the disciples, every man according to his ability,

152
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:25,459
determined to send relief

153
00:06:25,459 --> 00:06:29,019
unto the brethren which dwell in Judea.

154
00:06:29,019 --> 00:06:30,299
Notice it says in verse 30,

155
00:06:30,299 --> 00:06:34,640
which also they did and sent it to the elders

156
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:38,820
by the hands of Barnabas and Saul.

157
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:41,019
Saul's name is not changed to Paul

158
00:06:41,019 --> 00:06:42,459
until the first missionary journey,

159
00:06:42,459 --> 00:06:45,619
and we always refer to him as being the apostle Paul,

160
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,500
but the reality is that even before that journey,

161
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,859
while he's ministering in Antioch,

162
00:06:50,859 --> 00:06:53,459
there's this situation that takes place,

163
00:06:53,459 --> 00:06:55,619
and there's some saints, some believers,

164
00:06:55,619 --> 00:06:59,100
some brothers and sisters in Christ that are suffering.

165
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:02,459
And so the Bible tells us that they, the disciples,

166
00:07:02,459 --> 00:07:04,140
every man according to his ability,

167
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:05,260
notice in verse 29,

168
00:07:05,260 --> 00:07:08,459
determined to send relief unto the brethren

169
00:07:08,459 --> 00:07:09,940
which dwelt in Judea.

170
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:11,940
They wanted to, they were filled with

171
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:13,299
and led by the spirit of God.

172
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:14,779
They wanna send relief.

173
00:07:14,779 --> 00:07:17,299
They wanna help them with some finances,

174
00:07:17,299 --> 00:07:20,820
and they didn't just have good ideas or say,

175
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:22,899
this is a good idea that we would do this,

176
00:07:22,899 --> 00:07:26,040
but it says in verse 30, which also they did.

177
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:29,140
They fulfilled what God had laid upon their heart,

178
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:33,000
and we find that that offering was sent to the elders

179
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:36,859
by the hands of Barnabas and Saul.

180
00:07:36,859 --> 00:07:40,140
No doubt this provided for Paul an opportunity

181
00:07:40,140 --> 00:07:43,980
to be able to see how God would use his people

182
00:07:43,980 --> 00:07:45,660
to help his people.

183
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:47,899
What a blessing to consider this morning

184
00:07:47,899 --> 00:07:51,820
that God is at work and that God uses his people,

185
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:55,299
oftentimes even to be able to effectively minister

186
00:07:55,299 --> 00:07:59,579
and help others within the household of faith.

187
00:07:59,579 --> 00:08:01,579
We find that here in Acts chapter 11,

188
00:08:01,579 --> 00:08:04,100
if you fast forward to Acts chapter 20,

189
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:07,339
and in this passage of scripture in Acts chapter 20,

190
00:08:07,339 --> 00:08:11,299
really it's during the third missionary journey,

191
00:08:11,299 --> 00:08:12,940
and we find that as we come here

192
00:08:12,940 --> 00:08:15,179
to this portion of scripture,

193
00:08:15,179 --> 00:08:17,339
that the first, second missionary journey

194
00:08:17,339 --> 00:08:18,299
have been concluded,

195
00:08:18,299 --> 00:08:20,779
the church in Corinth has been established,

196
00:08:20,779 --> 00:08:23,859
and now Paul's out on this third missionary journey,

197
00:08:23,859 --> 00:08:26,000
and one of the things that Paul did

198
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,019
during the third missionary journey

199
00:08:28,019 --> 00:08:31,940
was he was working to be able to collect an offering

200
00:08:31,940 --> 00:08:34,539
for the saints that were suffering in Judea,

201
00:08:34,539 --> 00:08:36,580
and we find that the writing

202
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:39,179
of the book of 2 Corinthians

203
00:08:39,179 --> 00:08:42,020
and the timing of the third missionary journey

204
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:43,700
really coincide.

205
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:46,380
So why do we set this background and understanding?

206
00:08:46,380 --> 00:08:47,739
Because the apostle Paul,

207
00:08:47,739 --> 00:08:50,580
as he's writing the book of 2 Corinthians,

208
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:54,780
he's also there going forth on his third missionary journey

209
00:08:54,780 --> 00:08:57,940
in which God would use him to help raise some funds

210
00:08:57,940 --> 00:09:01,099
to help these believers that were suffering.

211
00:09:01,099 --> 00:09:04,460
And so as Paul would gather the leaders

212
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:07,140
of the church at Ephesus in Acts chapter number 20,

213
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:10,219
he tells them this, notice in verse 35,

214
00:09:10,219 --> 00:09:12,700
and he says after he's given them much instruction

215
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:14,700
with regard to his ministry in Ephesus

216
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,299
and their responsibilities,

217
00:09:16,299 --> 00:09:17,539
he says in verse 35,

218
00:09:17,539 --> 00:09:18,940
I have showed you all things,

219
00:09:18,940 --> 00:09:22,059
how that so laboring you ought to support the weak

220
00:09:22,059 --> 00:09:24,059
and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus,

221
00:09:24,059 --> 00:09:29,059
how he said it is more blessed to give than to receive.

222
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:31,780
And so the apostle Paul is mentioning this

223
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:35,400
specifically contextually to the church at Ephesus,

224
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,020
but I believe that this is probably a message

225
00:09:37,020 --> 00:09:39,659
that he shared with more than just the church at Ephesus,

226
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:42,299
it's simply recorded for us in scripture

227
00:09:42,299 --> 00:09:45,799
that he made this truth known to these believers in Ephesus.

228
00:09:45,799 --> 00:09:49,500
So Paul was concerned about helping these believers

229
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:52,500
that were in Judea, that were facing difficulty

230
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,919
and helping them with financial assistance.

231
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:57,940
Now look at 1 Corinthians chapter number 16,

232
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,500
and then we'll get to our text of scripture.

233
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,299
I'm laying all of this out for you.

234
00:10:01,299 --> 00:10:04,019
this groundwork so that we can understand

235
00:10:04,019 --> 00:10:07,359
kind of what's taking place in Paul's life

236
00:10:07,359 --> 00:10:10,119
and in his ministry and also with regard

237
00:10:10,119 --> 00:10:11,539
to the church there in Corinth

238
00:10:11,539 --> 00:10:13,939
and what some of their responsibility was

239
00:10:13,939 --> 00:10:17,499
and why Paul is writing the way that he is

240
00:10:17,499 --> 00:10:19,199
under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God

241
00:10:19,199 --> 00:10:20,259
to this local church.

242
00:10:20,259 --> 00:10:22,659
We find in 1 Corinthians 16,

243
00:10:22,659 --> 00:10:24,979
notice what Paul says in verse number one.

244
00:10:24,979 --> 00:10:28,339
Now concerning the collection for the saints,

245
00:10:28,339 --> 00:10:31,479
as I have given order to the churches of Galatia.

246
00:10:31,479 --> 00:10:33,959
Now that's the region where the churches

247
00:10:33,959 --> 00:10:37,039
during the first missionary journey were established.

248
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:39,119
So the church is in Galatia

249
00:10:39,119 --> 00:10:41,719
and so Paul says that he's given order to them,

250
00:10:41,719 --> 00:10:43,159
he's provided them with instruction

251
00:10:43,159 --> 00:10:45,759
and then he says even so do ye

252
00:10:45,759 --> 00:10:46,959
upon the first day of the week

253
00:10:46,959 --> 00:10:50,719
and let every one of you lay by him in store

254
00:10:50,719 --> 00:10:52,519
as God hath prospered him

255
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:54,679
that there be no gatherings when I come.

256
00:10:55,539 --> 00:10:57,999
And when I come, whomsoever you shall approve

257
00:10:58,659 --> 00:11:01,179
by your letters, then will I send to bring your,

258
00:11:01,179 --> 00:11:05,819
notice what he says, your liberality unto Jerusalem.

259
00:11:05,819 --> 00:11:08,539
He says and if it be me that I go also,

260
00:11:08,539 --> 00:11:10,619
they shall go with me.

261
00:11:10,619 --> 00:11:12,579
